<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2870: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-19T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                            1920—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>272. Department’s 112, March 30, 5 p.m.<note n="61" xml:id="d537fn61"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_521">p.
                                        521</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>Have you communicated to Foreign Office this Government’s approval of
                                Lamont notes? You should consult with your colleagues in this matter
                                as the Department is informed that the British Embassy at Tokyo has
                                been appropriately instructed. Has the Japanese Government formally
                                announced its approval of the notes?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>